  "plan": "I'll take a different approach: extract all '>' prompt lines from all frames, create a timeline of (frame_number, prompt_text) pairs, then reconstruct the ordered sequence by tracking how prompts grow and change. The key insight is that a command grows character by character, and when it's completed, the next command starts from empty. I'll group consecutive prefix-growth sequences and take the longest as the completed command.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 << 'PYEOF' > /app/moves_v4.txt\nimport os, re, glob\n\nfiles = sorted(glob.glob('/app/ocr/frame_*.txt'))\n\ndef get_prompts(text):\n    lines = text.strip().split('\\n')\n    prompts = []\n    for line in lines:\n        stripped = line.strip()\n        if stripped.startswith('>'):\n            cmd = stripped[1:].strip()\n            prompts.append(cmd)\n    return prompts\n\ndef get_counter(text):\n    m = re.search(r'Moves:\\s*(\\d+)', text)\n    return int(m.group(1)) if m else None\n\ndef clean(cmd):\n    cmd = cmd.strip()\n    while cmd and cmd[-1] in '._':\n        cmd = cmd[:-1]\n    if cmd.startswith('D') and len(cmd) > 1 and cmd[1].islower():\n        cmd = cmd[1:]\n    return cmd\n\ndef norm(cmd):\n    return clean(cmd).lower().replace(' ', '').replace(',', ',').strip()\n\ndef is_prefix(short, long):\n    \"\"\"Check if short is a prefix of long (allowing OCR noise).\"\"\"\n    short = norm(short)\n    long = norm(long)\n    if not short:\n        return True\n    if not long:\n        return False\n    if short == long:\n        return True\n    # Allow trailing _ in short as wildcard\n    short_base = short.rstrip('_')\n    if long.startswith(short_base):\n        return True\n    # Check if long starts with most of short\n    common = 0\n    for i in range(min(len(short_base), len(long))):\n        if short_base[i] == long[i]:\n            common += 1\n        else:\n            break\n    return common >= len(short_base) - 1 and common >= 2\n\nframe_data = []\nfor f in files:\n    text = open(f).read()\n    prompts = get_prompts(text)\n    counter = get_counter(text)\n    frame_data.append({\n        'file': os.path.basename(f),\n        'prompts': prompts,\n        'last': prompts[-1] if prompts else \"\",\n        'counter': counter\n    })\n\n# Approach: track the LAST prompt across frames.\n# When the last prompt grows (is an extension of previous), it's still being typed.\n# When it changes to something new (not an extension), the previous was completed.\nmoves = []\ncurrent_cmd = frame_data[0]['last']  # The command being typed\nprev_frame = frame_data[0]['file']\n\ndef is_typing_continuation(old, new):\n    \"\"\"Check if new is a continuation of old (same command being typed).\"\"\"\n    old_clean = clean(old)\n    new_clean = clean(new)\n    if not old_clean:\n        return False  # empty old means fresh prompt\n    if not new_clean:\n        return False  # empty new means fresh prompt (command completed)\n    return is_prefix(old, new)\n\nfor fd in frame_data[1:]:\n    new_last = fd['last']\n    \n    if is_typing_continuation(current_cmd, new_last):\n        # Same command, possibly more typed\n        current_cmd = new_last if len(new_last) > len(current_cmd) else current_cmd\n    else:\n        # Command changed - previous was completed\n        completed = clean(current_cmd)\n        if completed:\n            moves.append(completed)\n        current_cmd = new_last\n    \n    prev_frame = fd['file']\n\n# Last command\ncompleted = clean(current_cmd)\nif completed:\n    moves.append(completed)\n\n# Deduplicate consecutive identical/very similar moves\ndeduped = []\nfor m in moves:\n    if deduped and norm(m) == norm(deduped[-1]):\n        if len(m) > len(deduped[-1]):\n            deduped[-1] = m\n        continue\n    deduped.append(m)\n\nfor i, move in enumerate(deduped):\n    print(f\"{i+1}: {move!r}\")\n\nprint(f\"\\nTotal moves: {len(deduped)}\")\nprint(f\"Raw moves: {len(moves)}\")\ncounters = [(fd['file'], fd['counter']) for fd in frame_data if fd['counter'] is not None]\nif counters:\n    print(f\"Last counter: {counters[-1]}\")\nPYEOF\ncat /app/moves_v4.txt\n",
